&lt;div id=&#34;the-chaos-game&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Chaos Game&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this excellent &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCoxcjq-8xIDTYp3uz647V5A&#34;&gt;Numberphile&lt;/a&gt; video Ben Sparks demonstrates how to generate a fractal structure (the &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sierpinski_triangle&#34;&gt;Sierpinsky Triangle&lt;/a&gt;) by putting constraints (or rules) on a random process. The random process in this case is rolling a die, or, equivalently, drawing a random number from &lt;span class=&#34;math inline&#34;&gt;\(\mathcal{U}(1,6)\)&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
